The paper proposes a framework based on neural network ensembles to predict design rule violation hotspots using information from placement and global routing. This involves the use of machine learning techniques and optimization algorithms, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and optimization and control (cs.ET). The paper also deals with the physical design of integrated circuits, which falls under the sub-category of computer architecture (cs.AR). Additionally, the paper involves the use of predictive models to ensure manufacturability, which is related to the sub-categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and electromagnetics (cs.EM).
